column1: This sheet provides the mapping between the shorthand "dataset" name and the relevant CEDA metadata article(s)
Where possible a direct mapping between each "dataset" ID (column 1) and a relevant CEDA Metadata Catalogue object has been given.
In some cases more than one CEDA Metdata catlogue object has been listed - in cases where specific catalgoue entries have been identified these have been listed under columns C and D

However, where a more general reference to data from a particular campaign/project has been given, lacking an identifiable CEDA metadata cataglogue entry the "Dataset" entry reference is listed again in column F next to all relevant CEDA catalogue entries listed in H
Columns B and G are for CEDA internal purposes only to provide relevant mappings between objects and internal identifiers.
